<TITLE> JnU students demand punishment of BCL activist </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jagannath University, Apr 05 (bdnews24.com)  The students of the statistics department of Jagannath University suspended their classes on Monday demanding the punishment of a BCL activist following allegations that he hit a female student. The students said that they would not return to the class until Babu, a masters student of the mathematics department and a Bangladesh Chatra League activist, was punished Professor Mezbauddin, the vice-chancellor of the university said that an investigation committee had been formed and the student would be punished if he was found to be guilty. The students of the statistics department said that Babu assaulted one of their female class friends in front of the business faculty on April 1, and a general diary entry was filed in at the police station. The statistics department's students also made an application to Kazi Asadujjaman, the proctor, seeking improved security. The proctor assured them that he was taking appropriate steps. On Sunday, Rajshahi University authority banned a BCL activist on charges of assaulting a female student. bdnews24
